Description: Lower body sherd of grey ware pottery oinochoe, very dark grey fabric core and sandy edges with mica and limestone inclusions; dark burnished slip on exterior.
Curator's comments: Sherd joins 1924,1201.76.a. According to Perkins (2007) p. 60 #235, sherd 1924.1201.76.u belongs to same vessel as sherds 1924.1201.76.b-w but there is no mention of 1924,1201.76.a. Furthermore, there is no evidence that sherd 1924,1201.76.u joins any other sherd from group. Also according to Perkins, sherds 1888,0601.643b-d probably also join those listed above.
Bibliographic references: Etruscan Bucchero / A Catalogue of Etruscan Bucchero in the British Museum (No. 235)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GL.127)
